National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: INDIANAPOLIS, IN
Accident Number: CHI84LA275
Date & Time: 07/01/1984, 1030 EST
Registration: N21770
Aircraft: NORTH AMERICAN P-51 MUSTANG X
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Business
 Analysis A BOUNCED LANDING OCCURED DURING WHICH THE LEFT MAIN GEAR COLLAPSED FOLLOWED BY A GROUND LOOP.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: HARD LANDING Phase of Operation: LANDING - FLARE/TOUCHDOWN Findings 1.
(C) FLARE - MISJUDGED - PILOT IN COMMAND 2.
(F) LACK OF TOTAL EXPERIENCE IN KIND OF AIRCRAFT - PILOT IN COMMAND ---------- Occurrence #2: GEAR COLLAPSED Phase of Operation: LANDING - FLARE/TOUCHDOWN Findings 3.
